				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Do this for every dynamically animated object.<br /><br />- Check if there is enough DMA time.<br />- If not, don't update animation frame<br />- If so, continue<br />- Clear object's vram slot (area it takes up in VRAM) from the vram slot table<br />- Find new vram slot, using the vram slot table<br />- If slots are different, update animation frame<br />- If slots are the same, compare new and old animation frames<br />- If animation frames are the same, don't update animation frame<br />- If animation frames are different, update animation frame</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
